    "monster119": "<h1 class=monster>Corruption Corpse<br><span class=type>Medium natural animate (undead)</span><br><span class=level>Level 4 Artillery<span class=xp> XP 175</span></span> </h1> <p class=flavor><b>Initiative</b> +3        <b>Senses</b> Perception +3; Darkvision<br><b>Grave Stench</b> aura 1; living enemies in the aura take a -5 penalty to attack rolls.<br><b>HP</b> 46; <b>Bloodied</b> 23<br><b>Regeneration</b> 5 (if the corruption corpse takes radiant damage, regeneration doesn't function on its next turn)<br><b>AC</b> 17; <b>Fortitude</b> 16, <b>Reflex</b> 14, <b>Will</b> 14<br><b>Immune</b> disease, poison; <b>Resist</b> 10 necrotic; <b>Vulnerable</b> 5 radiant<br><b>Speed</b> 4</p><p class='flavor alt'>(⚔) <b>Slam</b> (standard, at-will) </p><p class=flavorIndent>+8 vs AC; 1d6+3 damage. </p><p class='flavor alt'>➶ <b>Mote of Corruption</b> (standard, at-will) ✦ <b>Necrotic</b></p><p class=flavorIndent>The corruption corpse hurls a black glob of necrotic filth; ranged 10; +7 vs Reflex; 2d6+3 necrotic damage, and the target is weakened (save ends). </p><p class='flavor alt'>ᗕ <b>Death Burst</b> ( when reduced to 0 hit points, ) ✦ <b>Necrotic</b></p><p class=flavorIndent>The corruption corpse explodes; close burst 1; +7 vs Fortitude; 2d6+3 necrotic damage. </p><p class='flavor alt'><b>Alignment</b> Unaligned       <b> Languages</b> -<br><b>Str</b> 16 (+5)      <b>Dex</b> 13 (+3)      <b>Wis</b> 12 (+3)<br><b>Con</b> 16 (+5)      <b>Int</b> 4 (-1)      <b>Cha</b> 3 (-2)</p><br><p class=publishedIn>Published in Monster Manual, page(s) 274, Open Grave, page(s) 70, 77, 78 , Dungeon Magazine 158, page(s) 96, Dungeon Magazine 176, page(s) 35, H1 Keep on the Shadowfell, page(s) 71.</p>",
    "monster3559": "<h1 class=monster>Deep Goblin Curser<br><span class=type>Small natural humanoid </span><br><span class=level>Level 4 Controller (Leader)<span class=xp> XP 175</span></span> </h1> <p class=flavor><b>Initiative</b> +4        <b>Senses</b> Perception +3; Darkvision<br><b>HP</b> 54; <b>Bloodied</b> 27<br><b>AC</b> 18; <b>Fortitude</b> 15, <b>Reflex</b> 16, <b>Will</b> 17<br><b>Speed</b> 6, climb 6</p><p class='flavor alt'>(⚔) <b>Stone Mace</b> (standard, at-will) ✦ <b>Weapon</b></p><p class=flavorIndent>+8 vs AC; 1d8 + 2 damage, and the target is slowed until the end of the deep goblin curser's next turn. </p><p class='flavor alt'>➶ <b>Caveroot Curse</b> (standard, at-will) </p><p class=flavorIndent>Ranged 10; +8 vs Reflex; 2d6 + 1 damage, and the target is restrained (save ends). </p><p class='flavor alt'>⚔ <b>Rage Rot Curse</b> (standard, recharge ⚄⚅) ✦ <b>Necrotic</b></p><p class=flavorIndent>Ranged 10; +8 vs Fortitude; . the target takes a –2 penalty to attack rolls until the end of the curser's next turn and, if it attacks during its next turn, it takes 2d6 + 6 necrotic damage.</p><p class='flavor alt'>➶ <b>Incite Bravery</b> (immediate reaction, when an ally uses goblin tactics, at-will) </p><p class=flavorIndent>Ranged 10; +8 vs or (whichever is lower); . the triggering ally can shift 2 more squares as a free action and make an attack as a free action.</p><p class='flavor alt'> <b>Goblin Tactics</b> (immediate reaction, when missed by a melee attack; at-will) </p><p class=flavorIndent>The deep goblin curser shifts 1 square.</p><p class='flavor alt'><b>Alignment</b> Unaligned       <b> Languages</b> Goblin<br><b>Skills</b> Stealth +11, Thievery +9<br><b>Str</b> 10 (+2)      <b>Dex</b> 15 (+4)      <b>Wis</b> 13 (+3)<br><b>Con</b> 14 (+4)      <b>Int</b> 9 (+1)      <b>Cha</b> 18 (+6)</p><p class='flavor alt'><b>Equipment</b>: stone mace, 2 potions of healing</p><br><p class=publishedIn>Published in Seekers of the Ashen Crown, page(s) 44.</p>",
